name: Holy Grail
description:
Grail - one of the popular western legends of the Middle Ages. The Grail was said to be used in the Last Supper, and at the Crucifixion receiving the blood that flowed from the spear in the side impact of Christ, even at this late date we still see the Importance and value of the Holy Grail from the catholic  ritual (holy communion) to adventure movies.
drawn and painted by me.

name: Rose Panther
description:
Roses - equivalent to the lotus of eastern culture. They are a symbol of love, love for something/someone. The rose is the most popular flower, male or female it works.
They have been used to represent passion, chastity, purity and beauty and not to forget love, as for their colors usually, yellow for joy, white devotion, admiration, or pink/red for compassion and love. In the past, the rose was a symbol of romance, 
But with spikes it can protect, a reminder that the beauty doesn't come without sacrifice. 

Panther, based on its freedom, he goes through the forests and nothing can stop him. He's top of the food chain, he lives his life his way. Something we as humans crave, the ability to do what we want.

drawn and painted by me.

name: Love Hurts
description:
Most, heart tattoos tend to represent love, passion, but there are other meanings for a heart tattoo. 
Some of the more common can include the following:

Bleeding: lost love

Broken: loss of a loved one, or a failed relationship

Pierced: tend to represent unforgetable and saddened memories of love

Hearts/dagger: bravery/betrayal.

Hearts/wings: freedom, spirit, free spirit

Sailor Jerry style dagger piercing through heart drawn and painted by me.
